= Intro ===============================================
eic_fastmc consists of three components, "acceptance,resolution,particle identification"
all three components are independent in code
"region" obtained from acceptance can be used as input for resolution and particle identification

It takes input
1. pid in PDG format(not implemented yet),
2. vertex P (GeV)
3. vertex Theta (deg)
4. vertex Phi (deg)
5. vertex E (GeV)
and return output
1. region accepted (0-8) or not accepted in any region (-1)
2. acceptance value (0-1)
3. resolution of dP/P(%), dTheta(deg), dPhi(deg), dz (cm)
4. Gaussian smeared P(GeV),Theta(deg),Phi(deg),E(GeV)
5.  probability of identifying this particle (0-1)

Use it as a class with info below
==================================================
#include "eic_fastmc.h"
eic_fastmc(const char detector[],const char version[],const char ebeam[],const char ibeam[],const char solenoid[],bool debug=false);  
int get_eic_fastmc(const int pid,const double * kin,int *region,double *acc,double *res,double *kin_smeared,double *pident,bool debug=false);
==================================================
Note to use "debug=true" to see more info

run example in root
.x test_eic_fastmc.C+ (test eic_fastmc)
.x test_all.C+ (test all three components individually)

read in a lund file, apply eic_fastmc, output another file
eic_fastmc_lund.C


= "detector region" ==============================================

We organize result in different detector regions (total 9)

region=0      ele downstream, dipole1side (temp for low E tagger) 
region=1      ele downstream, dipole3back (temp for high E tagger) 
region=2      central, barrel    
region=3      central, ionside
region=4      central, eleside outer
region=5      central, eleside inner
region=6      ion downtream, ec_iondownstream
region=7      ion forward, dipole2back (temp for some forward detector)
region=8      ion forward, dipole3back (temp for some forward detector)

